Before Cam broke his right arm, he could type 9 words per minute.
So in 5 minutes, he could type 9 * 5 = 45 words.
After he broke his arm, he could only type 6 words per minute using his left hand.
So in 5 minutes, he could type 6 * 5 = 30 words.
The difference between the number of words he could type before and after he broke his arm is 45 - 30 = 15.
Therefore, Cam can type 15 more words in 5 minutes after he broke his arm than before.
The answer is: 15
